                <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" source="#bib10536-1">The <bibl>New Testament (Philoxenian version)<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/10536"/>
          </bibl> is a revision of the
                        <bibl>New Testament (Peshitta version)<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/70"/>
          </bibl> commissioned by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/44">Philoxenos
                                of Mabbug</persName> and made by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/35">Polycarp, chorepiscopus of Mabbug</persName> in 507 or 508. It survives only in quotations
                    from <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/44">Philoxenos
                        of Mabbug</persName>'s own writings and possibly in a version of the Minor
                    Catholic Epistles and <bibl>Revelation<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/98"/>
          </bibl>.</note>
